page.title: 14LANDSCAPE
page.content:
THIS LAND IS FLAT AND IS HALF OPEN AREA AND HALF URBAN DEVELOPMENT. OF THE OPEN AREA THERE IA ROUGH RECREATIONAL SPACE AND A FORMAL M.O.D. PLAYING FIELD. THE REMAININ FIELDS ARE USED FOR GRAZING OR CROPS.
THE URBAN AREA IS MOSTLY COUNCIL HOUSING WITH A FEW HOUSES WHICH ARE PRIVATELY OWNED.
MANY HOUSES HAVE WELL TENDED GARDENS AND SOME HAVE ELABORATE FENCES AND HEDGES. THERE ARE A FEW OPEN AREAS OF GRASS IN FRONT OF SOME HOUSES WHICH THE COUNCIL HAVE LOOKED AFTER AND PLANTED WITH FLOWER BEDS. SOME GRASS AREAS HAVE BEEN MADE INTO CAR PARKS AS THE HOUSES WERE BUILT IN THE 1930s WHEN CARS WERE NOT COMMON.
